{{wikipedia|dab=wednesday (disambiguation)|wednesday}}
==English==

===Etymology===
{{etyl|enm}} (ca. 1200) ''[[Wednesdai]]'', not from {{etyl|ang}} ''[[wodnesdæg|wōdnesdæġ]]'', but rather from a ''*wednesdæġ'', attested as Old Frisian ''wednesdei''.
The compound translates to "[[Woden|Woden's]] day", as it were Common Germanic [[Appendix:Proto-Germanic/Wōdanas dagaz|Wōdinas dagaz]],
From the Old English theonym ''[[Woden]]'' and ''dæġ'' "[[day]]".

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˈwɛdənzdeɪ/}}, {{SAMPA|/"wEd@nzdeI/}} ''or'' {{IPA|/ˈwɛnzdeɪ/}}, {{SAMPA|/"wEnzdeI/}} ''or'' {{IPA|/ˈwɛdənzdi/}}, {{SAMPA|/"wEd@nzdi/}} ''or'' {{IPA|/ˈwɛnzdi/}}, {{SAMPA|/"wEnzdi/}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ˈwɛnzdeɪ/}}, {{SAMPA|/"wEnzdeI/}} ''or'' {{IPA|/ˈwɛnzdi/}}, {{SAMPA|/"wEnzdi/}}
* {{audio|en-us-Wednesday.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{audio|En-uk-Wednesday.ogg|Audio (UK)}}

