# {{obsolete}} To [[strike]], [[hit]]. #* '''1485''', Sir Thomas Malory, ''Le Morte Darthur'', Book VI: #*: and therewith was the knyght and the lady on one side – and suddeynly he '''swapped''' of the ladyes hede. # To exchange or give something in exchange for something else.
