==English==

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|/əˈbæk/}}, {{SAMPA|/@"b{k/}}
* {{rhymes|æk}}

===Etymology 1===
[[w:Middle English language|Middle English]] ''abak'', from [[w:Old English language|Old English]] ''on bæc'' "at, on, or toward the back"; formed as ''[[a-]]'' + ''[[back]]''

====Adverb====
{{en-adv|-}}

# {{rare}} Towards the back or [[rear]]; [[backwards]]; away.
#: ''Therewith '''aback''' she started.'' - [[w:Geoffrey Chaucer|Geoffrey Chaucer]]
# Behind; in the rear.
# {{nautical}} Backward against the [[mast]]; said of the sails when pressed by the wind from the "wrong" (forward) side.
#: ''By setting the foresail '''aback''' and the headsail in the middle one can bring a fore-and-aft rigged sailing boat practically to a halt even in heavy wind.''

=====Derived terms=====
* [[take aback]]

