==English==

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/əˈbæd(ə)n/}}

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|he}} {{term|אבדון|lang=he}} ''ābaddōn'', destruction, abyss, from {{Hebr|[[אבד]]}} ''ābad'', to be lost, to [[perish]].

===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun|s}}

# The [[destroyer]], or angel of the [[bottomless]] pit; -- the same as [[Apollyon]] and [[Asmodeus]].
# {{poetic}} Hell; the bottomless pit.
#: '''Quotations'''
#:* In all her gates, ''Abaddon'' rues Thy bold attempt. - [[w:John Milton|John Milton]]

