==English==
{{was wotd|2006|December|30}}
[[Image:Pinkabalone_300.jpg|thumb|right|Pink abalone.]]

===Etymology===
From American {{etyl|es|en}} {{term|abulón}}, from {{etyl|css|en}} ([[Rumsen]]) {{term|aulón}}. Used in English since the 19th Century.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/æbəˈləʊni/}}
* {{audio|en-us-abalone.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{US|Australia}} An edible [[univalve]] [[mollusc]] of the genus ''[[Haliotis]]'', having a shell lined with [[mother-of-pearl]].

====Synonyms====
* {{qualifier|UK}} [[ear-shell]],
* {{qualifier|Guernsey}} [[ormer]]
* {{qualifier|New Zealand}} [[pāua]], [[pawa]]
* {{qualifier|South Africa}} [[perlemoen]]

