==English==

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|/əˈbændənd/}}
* {{audio|en-us-abandoned.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Etymology 1===
Past tense of the verb ''to [[abandon]]''.

====Verb====
'''abandoned'''

# {{past of|abandon}}

===Etymology 2===
From the past participle of ''to [[abandon]]'', formed with ''[[-ed]]''.

====Adjective====
{{en-adj}}

# No longer maintained by its former owners, residents{{,}} or caretakers; [[forsaken]], [[deserted]].
#: ''Your '''abandoned''' streams.'' - [[Thomson]]
# No longer cared for by friends, family, etc.
#: ''After her parents died, the girl felt extremely '''abandoned'''.''
# [[self|Self]]-abandoned, or given up to vice; [[extremely]] wicked, or [[sinning]] without restraint; [[irreclaimably]] wicked ; as, an ''abandoned'' [[villain]].

