==English==
===Etymology=== {{etyl|enm}} {{term|abaissen}}, {{term|abaisshen}}, {{term|abashen}} etc., from a form (with lengthened stem) of {{etyl|fro}} {{term|esbaïr||}} ( > French {{term|ébahir}}), from {{term|es}} + {{term|bair||to [[astonish]]}}.
===Pronunciation=== * {{a|RP}} ** {{IPA|/əˈbæʃ/}} * {{audio|en-us-abash.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|æʃ}}
===Verb=== {{en-verb|abash|es}}
# {{transitive}} To make [[ashamed]]; to [[embarrass]]; to [[destroy]] the [[self-possession]] of; to [[confuse]] or [[confound]], as by exciting suddenly a [[consciousness]] of [[guilt]], [[mistake]], or [[inferiority]]; to put to shame; to [[disconcert]]; to [[discomfit]]. #: "''He was a man whom no check could '''abash'''''." - [[w:Thomas Babington Macaulay|Thomas Babington Macaulay]]. # {{intransitive|obsolete}} To lose self-possession; to become ashamed.
====Synonyms==== {{checksyns}} * [[confuse]] * [[confound]] * [[disconcert]] * [[shame]] * [[humiliate]] * [[embarrass]] * See also [[Wikisaurus:abash]]
====Usage notes==== * Of abash, [[confuse]], [[confound]]: '''Abash''' is a [[stronger]] word than '''confuse''', but not so strong as '''confound'''. ** We are ''abashed'' when struck either with sudden shame or with a [[humbling]] sense of inferiority; as, [[Peter]] was ''abashed'' by the look of his Master. So a [[modest]] youth is ''abashed'' in the presence of those who are greatly his superiors. ** We are ''confused'' when, from some [[unexpected]] or [[startling]] [[occurrence]], we lose [[clearness]] of thought and self-possession. Thus, a witness is often ''confused'' by a severe [[cross-]]examination; a [[timid]] person is apt to be ''confused'' in [[entering]] a room full of [[strangers]]. ** We are ''confounded'' when our minds are [[overwhelmed]], as it were, by something wholly unexpected, [[amazing]], dreadful, etc., so that we have nothing to say. Thus, a criminal is usually ''confounded'' at the [[discovery]] of his guilt. *::* Satan stood Awhile as mute, confounded what to say. - John Milton
====Derived terms==== * [[abashed]] * [[abashedly]] * [[abashedness]] * [[abashless]] * [[abashment]]
====Translations==== {{trans-top|to make ashamed, to embarrass}} * Bulgarian: {{t|bg|засрамвам}}, {{t|bg|смущавам}} * Czech: {{t-|cs|zahanbit}} * Dutch: {{t+|nl|beschamen}} * Finnish: [[saattaa häpeilemään]], [[saattaa hämille]] * French: {{t+|fr|confondre}} * German: {{t+|de|beschämen}} * [[Interlingua]]: [[confunder]] {{trans-mid}} * Japanese: [[狼狽]]させる(ろうばいさせる, roubaisaseru) * [[Macedonian]]: [[звунува]] (zbunuva) * Norwegian: {{t|no|gjøre skamfull}} * Portuguese: {{t+|pt|envergonhar}}, {{t+|pt|confundir}} * Russian: {{t+|ru|смущать}}, {{t|ru|конфузить|sc=Cyrl}}, {{t|ru|приводить в замешательство|sc=Cyrl}} * Spanish: {{t-|es|confundir}}, {{t|es|avergonzar}}, {{t|es|abochornar}} * Vietnamese: [[làm]] [[bối rối]], làm [[lúng túng]], làm [[luống cuống]], làm [[ngượng nghịu]] {{trans-bottom}}
