{{wikisource1911Enc|Abatement}} {{wikipedia}} ==English==
===Etymology=== From {{etyl|fro}} ''abatement'', {{etyl|fr}} ''[[abattement]]''.
===Pronunciation=== * {{audio|en-us-abatement.ogg|Audio (US)}}
===Noun=== {{en-noun}}
# The act of [[abating]], or the state of being [[abate]]d; a [[lessening]], [[diminution]], or reduction; removal or putting an end to; as, the '''abatement''' of a [[nuisance]] is the [[suppression]] [[thereof]]. # The amount abated; that which is taken away by way of reduction; [[deduction]]; [[decrease]]; a [[rebate]] or [[discount]] allowed. # {{heraldry}} A mark of [[dishonor]] on an [[escutcheon]]; any [[figure]] added to the [[coat of arms]] tending to lower the [[dignity]] or [[station]] of the [[bearer]]. # {{legal}} The [[entry]] of a [[stranger]], without right, into a [[freehold]] after the death of the last [[possessor]], before the heir or [[devisee]].
====Derived terms==== * [[defense in abatement]] * [[plea in abatement]]
