==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la}} {{term|abbreviatus|abbreviātus|lang=la}}, perfect passive participle of {{term|abbrevio|abbreviō|abbreviate|lang=la}}, formed from {{term|ad|lang=la}} + {{term|brevio|breviō|shorten|lang=la}}, from {{term|brevis||short|lang=la}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{rhymes|eɪt}}
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|/əˈbriːvieɪt/}}
* {{audio|en-us-abbreviate.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|abbreviat|ing}}

# {{transitive}} To make [[short]]er; to [[shorten]]; to [[abridge]]; to reduce by means of [[contraction]] or [[omission]], especially of [[word]]s written or spoken.
#* It is one thing to ''abbreviate'' by contracting, another by cutting off. — [[w:Francis Bacon|Francis Bacon]]
# {{mathematics}} To [[reduce]] to lower terms, as a [[fraction]].

====Related terms====
* [[abbreviation]]
* [[abbreviator]]

