===Etymology===
Established 1400–50. From late {{etyl|enm}} ''[[abbreviacioun]]'', from {{etyl|frm}} ''[[abréviation]]'', from {{etyl|LL.}} {{term|abbreviatio|abbreviātiō||lang=la}}, from {{term|ab||from|lang=la}} + {{term|abbrevio|abbreviō|shorten, abridge|lang=la}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|/əˌbriːviˈeɪʃən/}}
* {{rhymes|eɪʃən}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[shorten]]ed or [[contract]]ed form of a word or phrase, used to [[represent]] the whole: ''[[Dr]]''.
# The act or result of shortening or [[reduce|reducing]].
# {{music}} One or more dashes through the stem of a note, [[dividing]] it [[respectively]] into [[quavers]], [[semiquavers]], [[demisemiquavers]], or [[hemidemisemiquavers]].
# {{mathematics}} [[reduction|Reduction]] to lower [[term]]s, as a [[fraction]].

