==Latin==
===Verb=== {{la-verb-form|abdicant}}
# {{conjugation of|abdico|abdicō|3|p|pres|act|ind|lang=la}}
[[ar:abdicant]] [[ca:abdicant]] [[it:abdicant]] [[mg:abdicant]] [[ru:abdicant]] [[uk:abdicant]] [[vi:abdicant]] [[zh:abdicant]]

==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la}} {{term|abdicatus|abdicātus|lang=la}}, perfect passive participle of {{term|abdico|abdicō|abdicate|lang=la}}, formed from {{term|ab|lang=la}} + {{term|dico|dicō|proclaim, dedicate|lang=la}}, akin to {{term|dico|dīcō|say|lang=la}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|RP}}
** {{IPA|/ˈæbdɪkeɪt/}}
* {{a|US}}
** {{SAMPA|/{bdIkEt/}}
* {{audio|En-us-abdicate.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|abdicat|ing}}

# {{transitive}} To [[surrender]], [[renounce]] or [[relinquish]], as sovereign power; to [[withdraw]] [[definitely]] from filling or [[exercising]], as a high office, station, dignity; as, to ''abdicate'' the throne, the crown, the [[papacy]].
#: ''Note:'' The word ''abdicate'' was held to mean, in the case of James II, to abandon without a formal surrender.
#* {{rfdate}} [[w:Edward Gibbon|Edward Gibbon]]:
#*: The cross-bearers '''abdicated''' their service.
#* {{rfdate}} [[w:Edmund Burke|Edmund Burke]]:
#*: He '''abdicates''' all right to be his own governor.
#* {{rfdate}} [[w:James Anthony Froude|James Anthony Froude]]:
#*: The understanding '''abdicates''' its functions.
# {{transitive|obsolete}} To [[reject]]; to [[cast off]].
# {{transitive|legal}} To [[disclaim]] and [[expel]] from the family, as a father his child; to [[disown]]; to [[disinherit]].
# {{intransitive}} To relinquish or renounce a throne, or other high office or dignity; to renounce [[sovereignty]].
#* {{rfdate}} [[w:Edmund Burke|Edmund Burke]]:
#*: Though a king may '''abdicate''' for his own person, he cannot '''abdicate''' for the monarchy.

====Synonyms====
* {{sense|surrender, renounce, or relinquish}} [[give up]], [[relinquish]], [[renounce]], [[quit]], [[vacate]], [[surrender]], [[relent]]
* {{sense|reject; cast off}} [[forsake]], [[abandon]], [[desert]], [[renounce]], [[relent]]
* {{sense|disclaim and expel from family; disown; disinherit}} [[forsake]], [[give up]]
* {{sense|relinquish or renounce a high office or sovereignty}} [[relinquish]], [[renounce]], [[resign]], [[quit]], [[give up]], [[vacate]], [[relent]]

