==English==

===Etymology===
New Latin

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# One who [[abduct|abducts]], a [[kidnapper]].
# {{anatomy}} A [[muscle]] which serves to draw a part out, or form the [[median]] line of the body; as, the ''[[abductor oculi]]'', which draws the eye outward.

====Usage notes====
* The alternative spelling [[abductores]] is sometimes used for the plural of the anatomical muscle.

====Antonyms====
* [[abductee]] (One kidnapped)
* [[adductor]] (muscle)

