===Etymology===
From {{etyl|ONF.}} {{term|able|lang=xno}}, variant of {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|habile|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|habilis|lang=la}}, from {{term|habeo|habeō|have, hold|lang=la}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈeɪ.bl̩/|/ˈeɪ.bəl/}}, {{SAMPA|1=/eIbl=/|2=/eIb@l/}}
* {{audio|en-us-able.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|eɪbəl}}
* {{hyphenation|a|ble}}
* {{homophones|Abel}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|abl|er}}

# {{dated}} [[healthy|Healthy]].
#: ''After the past week of forced marches, only half the men are fully '''able'''.''
# [[permit|Permit]]ted to; not [[prevent]]ed from; having the power or capacity to.
#: ''With that obstacle removed, I am now '''able''' to proceed with my plan.''
#: ''I’m only '''able''' to visit you when I have other work here.''
#: ''I’ll see you as soon as I’m '''able'''.''
# [[skillful|Skillful]].
#: ''The chairman was also an '''able''' sailor.''
# {{legal}} [[legal|Legally]] [[qualify|qualified]] or [[competent]].
#: ''In most states, such a person is not '''able''' to inherit property.''

====Synonyms====
* See also [[Wikisaurus:skillful]]

