==English== {{was wotd|2011|September|29}} ===Etymology=== From the {{etyl|la|en}} ''[[abnegatus]]'', past participle of ''[[abnegare]]'', formed from ''[[ab-]]'' + ''[[negare]]'' "to deny".
===Pronunciation=== * {{a|RP}} {{IPA|/ˈæbnɪɡeɪt/}} * {{audio|En-us-abnegate.ogg|Audio (US)}}
===Verb=== {{en-verb|abnegat|ing}}
# {{transitive}} To [[deny]] (oneself something); to [[renounce]] or give up (a right, a power, a [[claim]], a privilege, a convenience). #* '''1898''' December 10, ''Asbell v. State'', reported in ''The Pacific Reporter'', volume 55, page 339: #*: To compel a state, upon theories of doubtful statutory interpretation, to appear as defendant suitor in its own courts, and to litigate with private parties as to whether it had '''abnegated''' its sovereignty of exemption, would be intolerable. # {{transitive}} To [[reject]], to [[deny]]. #* '''1875''' January, ''Brownson's Quarterly Review'', page 20: #*: All ancient and modern histories of nations '''abnegate''' God.
====Derived terms==== * [[abnegator]]
====Related terms==== * [[abnegation]]
====Translations==== {{trans-top|to deny oneself something}} * Finnish: {{t|fi|kieltää}} {{trans-mid}} * German: [[entsagen]] * {{trreq|es}} {{trans-bottom}}
{{trans-top|to reject, to deny}} * Finnish: {{t|fi|torjua}}, {{t|fi|kieltää}} {{trans-mid}} * {{trreq|es}} {{trans-bottom}}
=====Translations to be checked===== {{checktrans}} * {{ttbc|bg}}: отричам, отхвърлям, отказвам (се от) * {{ttbc|vi}}: [[nhịn]], [[bỏ]], [[từ bỏ]], [[từ chối không nhận]]
