==English==
===Etymology=== Derivative of [[abort]] ===Noun=== {{en-noun}}
# {{obsolete}} [[abortion]]

==English==
===Etymology=== From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|abounden|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|fro}} {{term|abonder|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|la}} {{term|abundare|abundāre|lang=la}}, present active infinitive of {{term|abundo|abundō|overflow|lang=la}}, which comes from {{term|ab||from, down from|lang=la}} + {{term|undo|undō|surge, swell; overflow with|lang=la}}.
===Pronunciation=== * {{a|RP}} {{IPA|/əˈbaʊnd/}} * {{audio|en-us-abound.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*: {{rhymes|aʊnd}}
===Verb=== {{en-verb}}
# {{intransitive}} To be [[plentiful]]; to be very [[prevalent]]; to [[overflow]]. #* The wild boar which '''abounds''' in some parts of the continent of Europe. - Chambers. #* Where sin '''abounded''' grace did much more '''abound'''. ''Romans 5:20''. # {{intransitive}} To be [[copiously]] supplied; to be [[wealthy]] in; to [[teem]] with; -- followed by ''in'' or ''with''. #: ''The wilderness '''abounds''' in traps.''
====Derived terms==== * [[abounder]] * [[aboundingly]] * [[abound in]] * [[abound with]]
====Related terms==== * [[abundance]] * [[abundant]]
====Translations==== {{trans-top|to be plentiful}} * Bulgarian: [[изобилствам]] * Dutch: [[overvloedig]] [[aanwezig]] [[zijn]] * Finnish: [[olla]] [[runsaasti]], [[olla]] [[tulvillaan]] * French: {{t+|fr|foisonner}} * German: im [[Überfluss]] [[vorhanden]] [[sein]] * Italian: [[abbondare]], [[essere abbondante]] {{trans-mid}} * [[Mapudungun]]: {{tø|arn|ünüfn}} * [[Novial]]: [[abunda]] * Portuguese: [[abundar]], [[ser abundante]] * Romanian: {{t-|ro|abunda}} * Spanish: [[abundar]], [[ser]] [[abundante]] {{trans-bottom}}
{{trans-top|to be copiously supplied}} * Czech: {{t-|cs|oplývat}} * Dutch: [[wemelen]] (van) * Finnish: [[olla]] [[runsaasti]], [[olla]] [[tulvillaan]] * French: {{t+|fr|abonder}} * Hungarian: {{t|hu|bővelkedik}} {{trans-mid}} * Italian: [[abbondare]], [[essere abbondante]] * [[Novial]]: [[abunda]] * Portuguese: [[abundar]], [[ser abundante]] * Spanish: [[abundar]], [[ser]] [[abundante]] {{trans-bottom}}
