==English==

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPAchar|/ə-bŭv/}}, (''[[Received Pronunciation|UK]]''){{IPA|/əˈbʌv/}}, {{SAMPA|/@"bVv/}}
* {{rhymes|ʌv}}
* {{audio|en-us-above.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Etymology===
{{etyl|ang}} {{term|abufan|ābufan|lang=ang}}. Cognate with Danish {{term|oven|lang=da}}, Dutch {{term|boven|lang=nl}}, German {{term|oben|lang=de}}, Swedish {{term|ovan|lang=sv}}.

===Preposition===
{{en-prep}}

# In or to a higher place; higher than; on or over the upper surface; over; — opposed to ''below'' or ''beneath''.
#* {{rfdate}} translation of [[w:Genesis|Genesis]] 2:20,
#*: Fowl that may fly '''above''' the earth.
# Figuratively, higher than; superior to in any respect; [[surpassing]]; beyond; higher in measure or degree than; as, things ''above'' [[comprehension]]; ''above'' mean actions; conduct ''above'' reproach.
#* {{rfdate}} [[w:Marlowe|Marlowe]],
#*: Thy worth […] is actions '''above''' my gifts.
#* {{rfdate}} translation of [[w:Acts|Acts]] 36:13,
#*: I saw in the way a light from heaven '''above''' the brightness of the sun.
# [[surpassing|Surpassing]] in number or quantity; more than; as, ''above'' a hundred. (Passing into the [[adverbial]] sense; see adverb #4 below.)

