==English==
===Etymology=== Mid-15th century, {{prefix|a|t1=on, of|breast|t2=chest|ps=2}}, in sense “breasts (chests) in line, side-by-side and exactly equally advanced”;<ref name="oetyld">{{R:Online Etymology Dictionary}}</ref> roughly “breast-by-breast”. Other senses of “equally advanced” developed metaphorically. Phrase ''keep abreast'' “keep informed, up to the same level as oneself” is from the 1650s.<ref name="oetyld" />
===Pronunciation=== * {{audio|en-us-abreast.ogg|Audio (US)}}
===Adverb=== {{en-adv}}
# Informed, well-informed, familiar, acquainted # Side by side, facing forward, with breasts in a line; as, #:* Two men could hardly walk '''abreast'''. - [[w:Thomas Babington Macaulay|Thomas Babington Macaulay]] # {{nautical}} Side by side; also, opposite; over against; on a line with the [[vessel]]'s beam; – with ''of''. # Up to a certain level or line; [[equally]] advanced; as, to keep '''abreast''' of [or with] the present state of science. # {{obsolete}}: At the same time; [[simultaneously]] #:* '''Abreast''' [[therewith]] began a [[convocation]]. - [[w:Thomas Fuller|Thomas Fuller]]
====Synonyms==== * {{sense|informed}} {{l|en|apprised}}, {{l|en|up to date}}/{{l|en|up-to-date}}
====Translations==== {{trans-top|informed}} * Dutch: [[op de hoogte]], [[bekend]], [[goed ingelicht]], [[welingelicht]] * Estonian: {{t|et|kursis}} * Finnish: [[tietoinen]], [[ajan tasalla]] * French: {{t+|fr|au courant}} * German: [[auf dem Laufenden]] {{trans-mid}} * Italian: [[essere aggiornato]], [[stare al passo]] (con i [[tempi]], con le [[notizie]]), [[mantenersi al corrente]] * Portuguese: [[bem]] [[informado]] * Spanish: [[al corriente]] {{trans-bottom}}
{{trans-top|side by side}} * Bulgarian: [[редом]], [[един до друг]], [[на един ред]], [[рамо до рамо]] * Dutch: [[zij aan zij]] * Finnish: [[rinnakkain]], [[vierekkäin]], [[vierivieressä]] * French: {{t+|fr|côte à côte}} * German: [[beieinander]] {{trans-mid}} * Italian: [[affiancato]], [[di pari passo]] * Polish: [[obok siebie]] * Portuguese: [[lado a lado]] * Russian: {{t|ru|в ряд}}, {{t|ru|на одной линии}} * Spanish: [[de lado a lado]] {{trans-bottom}}
{{trans-top|nautical: side by side; also, opposite; over against; on a line with the vessel's beam}} * Finnish: {{t-|fi|kyljittäin}} * Italian: [[al traverso]] {{trans-mid}} * Russian: {{t|ru|на одной линии}}, {{t|ru|на траверзе}}, {{t|ru|борт о борт}} {{trans-bottom}}
