==English== {{Webster 1913}}
===Alternative forms=== * [[abridgement]]
===Etymology=== From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|abregement|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|frm}}; see {{term|abridge}}.
===Noun=== {{en-noun}}
# {{US}} The act of [[abridging]], or the state of being [[abridged]]; [[diminution]]; [[lessening]]; reduction or [[deprivation]]; as, an '''abridgment''' of pleasures or of [[expenses]]. # {{US}} An [[epitome]] or [[compend]], as of a book; a [[shortened]] or abridged form; an [[abbreviation]]. #:* Ancient coins as '''abridgments''' of history. - [[w:Joseph Addison|Joseph Addison]] # {{obsolete}} That which [[abridges]] or cuts short; hence, an entertainment that makes the time pass quickly #:* What '''abridgment''' have you for this evening? What masque? what music? - Shakespeare, ''Midsummer Night's Dream, V-i''
====Usage notes==== * In current usage this spelling is about as common as {{term|abridgement}} in the US, but much less common in the UK. * Notes on near-synonyms: ** An ''abridgment'' is made by [[omitting]] the less important parts of some larger work; as, an ''abridgment'' of a [[dictionary]]. ** A [[compendium]] is a brief [[exhibition]] of a subject, or science, for common use; as, a ''compendium'' of American literature. ** An [[epitome]] corresponds to a ''compendium'', and gives [[briefly]] the most material points of a subject; as, an ''epitome'' of history. ** An [[abstract]] is a brief statement of a thing in its main points. ** A [[synopsis]] is a [[bird's-eye]] view of a subject, or work, in its several parts.
====Synonyms==== * {{sense|act of abridging}} [[compendium]], [[epitome]], [[abstract]], [[synopsis]], [[précis]]
====Related terms==== * [[abridge]]
====Translations==== {{trans-top|act of abridging}} * Dutch: [[bekorting]], [[verkorting]]. {{trans-mid}} {{trans-bottom}} {{trans-top|shortened form}} * Dutch: ingekorte versie, [[uitreksel]], korte inhoud. {{trans-mid}} * Spanish: {{t|es|compendio}}, {{t|es|resumen}} {{trans-bottom}}
===External links=== * {{R:Webster 1913}} * {{R:Century 1911}} * {{R:OneLook}}
